cast.overview: Joe Gideon is at the top of the heap, one of the most successful directors and choreographers in musical theater. But he can feel his world slowly collapsing around him - his obsession with work has almost destroyed his personal life, and only his bottles of pills keep him going.
cast.title: All That Jazz

details.biography: Nicole Providence Fosse was born on March 3, 1963 to perhaps the most famous Broadway couple ever: Gwen Verdon and Bob Fosse. Gwen Verdon, the famed petite, redhaired triple-threat, and Bob Fosse, the workaholic choreographer, were married in 1960, and shortly thereafter decided to have children. Nicole was Fosse's only child, and Gwen's second. Nicole has taken various roles in her father's films, and, in 1999, teamed with her mother to create the Broadway smash "Fosse".
details.name: Nicole Fosse
